//<br />
Tear gas, formally known as a lachrymator agent or lachrymator (from the Latin lacrima, meaning &quot;tear&quot;), sometimes colloquially known as mace,[NB 1] is a chemical weapon that causes severe eye and respiratory pain, skin irritation, bleeding, and even blindness. In the eye, it stimulates the nerves of the lacrimal gland to produce tears. Common lachrymators include pepper spray (OC gas), PAVA spray (nonivamide), <span style="color: red;">CS gas, CR gas, CN gas (phenacyl chloride), bromoacetone, xylyl bromide, syn-propanethial-S-oxide (from onions), and Mace (a branded mixture), and household vinegar. </span><br />
//<br />
巴打會唔會試下check其他teargas料睇下中唔中

